Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of eight (8) years, three (3) years initial confinement, followed by five (5) years extended supervision.   Execution of sentence is stayed and defendant is placed on probation to DOC for seven and one-half (7 1/2) years.   Conditions of probation are:
1) Maintain full-time employment; 
2) Obtain GED/HSED; 
3) Maintain absolute sobriety; 
4) Pay costs of action; 
5) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC; 
6) AODA assessment and follow through; 
7) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process; 
8) Spend twelve (12) months in jail, under the Huber Law, to commence today; 
9) Submit DNA sample and pay surcharge.   
Court finds the defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and for the Substance Abuse Program.   
Defendant is entitled to 1 day credit if revoked.   
